# SecScan ignore file
# Add vulnerability IDs or rule IDs to suppress known findings.
# One pattern per line. Use # for comments.
#
# Examples:
#   CVE-2023-12345
#   semgrep.rule.id
#   GHSA-xxxx-yyyy-zzzz  # reason: accepted risk

# Suppress a specific CVE (accepted risk after review)
# CVE-2023-12345  # reason: not exploitable in our context

# Suppress a semgrep rule
# javascript.lang.security.audit.detect-non-literal-regexp  # reason: false positive

# Suppress a GHSA advisory
# GHSA-abcd-efgh-ijkl  # reason: mitigated by WAF
